        {
            "body": "Some notes on modularization:\r\n\r\nGoals: better support new use cases, e.g websockets, Forge, cross-version, auto-negotiation, browser, and future unexpected usage\r\n\r\nLogical components (basic building blocks):\r\n\r\n* [x] Data/protocol specifications: minecraft-data, node-minecraft-data\r\n* [x] Compressor: src/transforms/compression.js, zlib deflate, threshold\r\n* [x] Framer: src/transforms/framing.js - note: ws disable\r\n* [x] Serializer: src/transforms/serializer.js packet stream\r\n* [ ] Keep-alive: respond to keep-alive packets for server (in this PR)\r\n* [ ] Ping: responds to ping in the server (in this PR)\r\n * [ ] FE01 ping https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/issues/332\r\n* [ ] Login: handle client logins in the server (in this PR), onEncryptionKeyResponse, loginClient, ursa..\r\n* [ ] Login/handshake client: onEncryptionKeyResponse, yggdrasil, ...\r\n* [ ] Encryption: usually a consequence of handshaking (but not always https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/issues/289)\r\n* [ ] `set_protocol` client: version, host (changed by FML), port, next state 2\r\n * [ ] Client ping: also uses `set_protocol` but different next state 1\r\n* [ ] `FML|HS` handshake (nmp-forge): change host, handshake on plugin channels\r\n* [ ] Plugin channels: streams, registration, https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/pull/328\r\n* [ ] DNS SRV resolution (createClient connect)\r\n* [ ] TCP sockets (`net`): usual final endpoint to the stream\r\n\r\nAdvanced usage (compose from above and other components):\r\n\r\n* [ ] Cross-version dynamic https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/issues/234 (nmp-auto) = client ping (FE01?) +`set_protocol` + `FML|HS`\r\n* [ ] Websocket-compatible = data + compressor + serializer + keepalive; without: framer (ws msgs), TCP, login/handshake (token), encryption (wss://). https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/pull/320 Client stream / wsmc\r\n* [ ] Browser = websocket-compatible + `websocket-stream`/`worker-stream` (3rd party modules)\r\n* [ ] Web-based Minecraft client = browser + mineflayer + voxel.js (etc.)\r\n* [ ] Proxy = ...\r\n",
